Chilean Stocks: Empresas Iansa, Empresas La Polar, Lan Airlines

-- B y   J a m e s   A t t w o o d
-- 
2011-07-21T22:23:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/chilean-stocks-empresas-iansa-empresas-la-polar-lan-airlines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:14 p.m.  New York  time.  The Ipsa index climbed 0.3 percent to 4,618.04.  Empresas Iansa SA (IANSA)   rose 1.7 percent to 49.75
pesos after two days of declines. Chile’s largest sugar producer
gained in line with the price of the sweetener in New York.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)  , the Chilean department-
store chain that set aside $900 million last month to cover
consumer-lending irregularities, fell 8.3 percent to a record
low of 459.59 pesos. The stock has lost 17 percent this week
after regulators gave the company through October to submit
financial statements that incorporate the additional provisions.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)  , scheduled to report second-
quarter earnings on July 27, rose 0.5 percent to 13,276 pesos.
 United Continental Holdings Inc. (UAL) , the world’s largest airline,
reported second-quarter profit today that topped analysts’
estimates as higher fares helped blunt rising fuel costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Attwood in Santiago at 
